# Small Slice Execution Guidance

Use this rule for implementation work to reduce regression risk and keep progress verifiable.

## Default behavior

- Prefer one vertical slice at a time:
  - backend/API change
  - frontend integration (if needed)
  - tests
  - docs/changelog/release notes
- After finishing one slice, prompt the user to validate and decide whether to continue.

## User alert requirement

Before starting a second major slice in the same pass, explicitly notify the user:

- first slice is complete
- what was validated
- recommendation to stop and verify now

## Flexibility

- If user wants to continue immediately, proceed.
- Do not block progress when the user explicitly asks to keep going.
- Keep reminding briefly that smaller validated slices catch bugs earlier.

## Suggested checkpoint language

- "Slice 1 is complete and validated. Recommended: stop here and verify behavior before slice 2. If you want, I can continue now."
